EWS/B31509106.397218653;dc_trk_aid=3D587194800;dc_trk_cid=3D211990113;dc_la=
t=3D;dc_rdid=3D;tag_for_child_directed_treatment=3D;tfua=3D;ltd=3D;dc_tdv=
=3D1?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F12%2F24%29&utm_content=
=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F6%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_=
source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a )

Indeed, Freda has effectively, if belatedly, pushed for modernization. He h=
as since reversed himself and committed his brands to partnerships with Ama=
zon, once an unspeakable notion at Est=C3=A9e Lauder. (As of this week, Too=
 Faced now has an official presence on Amazon, following on the heels of Cl=
inique.) The longtime reluctance is reminiscent of the company=E2=80=99s la=
bored decision to belatedly enter Sephora and Ulta. =E2=80=9CThey have to t=
urn around and now allow their brands to go on Amazon,=E2=80=9D this person=
 added. =E2=80=9CThey=E2=80=99re doing it from a place of desperation.=E2=
=80=9D

In the meantime, Freda remains intent on =E2=80=9Cowning the night,=E2=80=
=9D his attempt to compete against L=E2=80=99Or=C3=A9al, which he believes =
=E2=80=9Cowns the day,=E2=80=9D according to the current Lauder executive. =
Others have described a fixation with nighttime products=E2=80=93=E2=80=93w=
hich include skincare, makeup, and
fragrance=E2=80=94as a =E2=80=9Cone-size-fits-all=E2=80=9D approach that fa=
ils to take brand, price, and category expertise into consideration. Freda =
is still trying to re-create the success of flagship brand Est=C3=A9e Laude=
r=E2=80=99s 42-year-old hero product, Advanced Night Repair, even when it d=
oesn=E2=80=99t necessarily make sense. Some notable recent examples include=
 makeup line Bobbi Brown=E2=80=99s pricey serum that =E2=80=9Cnourishes ove=
rnight,=E2=80=9D and Jo Malone London=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cnight collection=
=E2=80=9D of fragrances. =E2=80=9CYou can charge higher price points,=E2=80=
=9D this person said of night-specific products like serums and richer crea=
ms. =E2=80=9CJust because people will spend more at night, Fabrizio believe=
s that there=E2=80=99s more of an opportunity to win there.=E2=80=9D Freda =
encouraged cosmetics brands to create products marketed specifically for th=
e evening, too.

Additionally, Freda pushed makeup brands to develop skincare=E2=80=93=E2=80=
=93even if they had no authority to do so=E2=80=93=E2=80=93because it was i=
nexpensive to make, and they could
charge more money than they could for a lipstick or foundation. It was also=
 another way to reach the skincare-obsessed Chinese consumer that the compa=
ny relied on during the boom years. When MAC launched skincare in January o=
f last year, I heard that Freda pulled Clinique=E2=80=99s longtime product =
development lead, Janet Pardo, to work on the inaugural lineup. =E2=80=9CMA=
C doing skincare was a Fabrizio top-down directive,=E2=80=9D another curren=
t executive said. =E2=80=9CWe were all sitting there saying, No one is goin=
g to buy this.=E2=80=9D

It=E2=80=99s hard to tell a simple story about which of Freda=E2=80=99s ini=
tiatives has and hasn=E2=80=99t worked. His focus on artisanal, or higher-e=
nd, perfume seems to be paying off: Lauder=E2=80=99s fragrance business has=
 grown in 11 of the past 12 quarters, I=E2=80=99m told, driven by Le Labo (=
a 2014 acquisition), Jo Malone, and Tom Ford. At the same time, while the E=
st=C3=A9e Lauder Companies stock is down almost 70 percent from an all-time=
 high in 2021, it has
also almost doubled in 10 years while paying a hefty dividend. The collapse=
 of the share price from its pandemic-era high must surely bother the famil=
y, which owns 38 percent of the common stock (and 86 percent of the voting =
stock). But a family concern like Lauder is also accustomed to thinking in =
decades, not years. And Freda won=E2=80=99t be replaced until they say so=
=E2=80=94whether his successor is in the family or not.

That=E2=80=99s it from Rachel and me. One question for you. Who isn=E2=80=
=99t ( https://www.nytimes.com/2024/06/08/style/who-is-a-rodent-man.html?ut=
m_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F12%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+=
Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F6%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=
=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) a rodent man?

Until tomorrow,
Lauren

